======================================================================
UNIFIED MECHANISM: QR SYMMETRY vs CONSECUTIVENESS
======================================================================

======================================================================
p = 7, m = 3
======================================================================

  VIEW 1: SPECTRAL
  Paley |λ|: ['1.414', '1.414', '1.414']
  Interval |λ|: ['2.247', '0.555', '0.802']
  IPR: Paley=0.3333 (flat), Interval=0.7222 (peaked)
  Paley spectrum is FLAT

  VIEW 2: TOPOLOGICAL (eigenspace anomaly)
  Paley:    k=0 anomaly depth D=4, β=[1,0,0,0,6,0,0], χ=7
  Interval: k=0 anomaly depth D=1, β=[1,1,0,0,0,0,0], χ=0
  Paley: QR group creates deep anomaly via multiplicative closure
  Interval: no extra symmetry → trivial acyclic eigenspaces

  VIEW 3: COMBINATORIAL (co-occurrence)
  Paley: co_occ_k(d) = CONSTANT (QR difference set)
  Interval: co_occ_k(d) = a_k + C(m-2,k-3)*d (THM-143 gradient)
    k=3: Interval slope = C(1,0) = 1
    k=5: Interval slope = C(1,2) = 0
    k=7: Interval slope = C(1,4) = 0

  VIEW 4: H-MAXIMALITY
  Paley H=189, Interval H=175 → Paley WINS (α₁ dominates)
  α_max = floor(7/3) = 2

  GRADIENT-TO-ALPHA SCALING:
    (3,3) pair: b_k² = 1, Δα₂ scales as O(p^2)
    (5,5) pair: b_k² = 0, Δα₂ scales as O(p^6)
    (7,7) pair: b_k² = 0, Δα₂ scales as O(p^10)

======================================================================
p = 11, m = 5
======================================================================

  VIEW 1: SPECTRAL
  Paley |λ|: ['1.732', '1.732', '1.732', '1.732', '1.732']
  Interval |λ|: ['3.513', '0.521', '1.204', '0.594', '0.764']
  IPR: Paley=0.2000 (flat), Interval=0.6889 (peaked)
  Paley spectrum is FLAT

  VIEW 2: TOPOLOGICAL (eigenspace anomaly)
  Paley:    k=0 anomaly depth D≥6, β=[1,0,0,0,0,5,15,0,0,0,0], χ=11
  Interval: k=0 anomaly depth D=1, β=[1,1,0,...,0] (conj), χ=0
  Paley: QR group creates deep anomaly via multiplicative closure
  Interval: no extra symmetry → trivial acyclic eigenspaces

  VIEW 3: COMBINATORIAL (co-occurrence)
  Paley: co_occ_k(d) = CONSTANT (QR difference set)
  Interval: co_occ_k(d) = a_k + C(m-2,k-3)*d (THM-143 gradient)
    k=3: Interval slope = C(3,0) = 1
    k=5: Interval slope = C(3,2) = 3
    k=7: Interval slope = C(3,4) = 0

  VIEW 4: H-MAXIMALITY
  Paley H=95095, Interval H=93027 → Paley WINS (α₁ still dominates)
  α_max = floor(11/3) = 3

  GRADIENT-TO-ALPHA SCALING:
    (3,3) pair: b_k² = 1, Δα₂ scales as O(p^2)
    (5,5) pair: b_k² = 9, Δα₂ scales as O(p^6)
    (7,7) pair: b_k² = 0, Δα₂ scales as O(p^10)

======================================================================
THE GRAND UNIFICATION
======================================================================

QR Multiplicative Closure (Paley):
  SPECTRAL:      |λ_t| = √((p+1)/4) for all t  (Gauss sum)
  TOPOLOGICAL:   k=0 eigenspace anomaly → deep homology (β_{(p+1)/2} = p-1)
  COMBINATORIAL: Uniform multiplicity → high α₁, low α₂+
  H-EFFECT:      Wins at small p (α₁ dominance)

Consecutive-Integer Structure (Interval):
  SPECTRAL:      |λ_t| = |sin(πmt/p)/sin(πt/p)|  (Dirichlet kernel)
  TOPOLOGICAL:   No anomaly → acyclic eigenspaces → β=[1,1,0,...,0]
  COMBINATORIAL: Distance gradient → co-occ linearity → high α₂+
  H-EFFECT:      Wins at large p (α₂+ dominance via O(p^6) scaling)

The SAME property — QR closure vs consecutiveness — simultaneously
determines ALL four characteristics. They are not independent
phenomena but manifestations of a single algebraic distinction.

Phase transition at p≈13:
  The gradient-to-alpha scaling O(p^{2k-4}) means higher-order
  disjointness (α_2, α_3) grows POLYNOMIALLY faster than
  multiplicity advantage (α_1). The crossover occurs when:
    2^2 * Δα₂ > 2 * Δα₁
  i.e., when the disjointness bonus outweighs the multiplicity penalty.

Topological side:
  The phase transition does NOT change the topological type.
  Both before and after p≈13, Interval has β=[1,1,0,...,0].
  The topology is a STATIC invariant, while H-maximality is DYNAMIC.
  Topology reflects the SYMMETRY TYPE, not the H value.

DONE.
